SaveMe
Android app "Save Me" project for Mobile development course UAB

Save Me is an Android app developed with Android Studio This application was created to be used in emergency situations or natural disasters, it can help you find it easier for rescue teams.

The Save Me app gives you some important tools for emergency situations:

SOS flashlight - turn on the flashlight and send SOS light signal
Where I am? - show your current location on map and give you quick acces to GoogleNavigation
Send my Location - indicate your current position with cordinates(lattitude and longitude) and allows you to send the coordinates via an SMS
Emergency Call - call the emergency number
Family Call - call the family phone number defined in section Settings
Settings - define your emergency family phone number, enable/disable gps and other permissions.
